          "body": "The chapter ends with a cascading chain of responsive blessing: God responds to the heavens, the heavens to the earth, the earth to the grain and wine and oil, and they respond to Jezreel (2:21-22). The very agricultural bounty that Israel credited to Baal (2:5) and that God took back (2:9) now flows through a chain of responsive creation, each element answering the next in ordered harmony — because the relationship between God and His people is restored. Then 2:23 reverses every covenant curse of chapter 1 with three divine speech-acts: 'I will sow her' (Jezreel redeemed), 'I will have compassion on her who had not obtained compassion' (Lo-ruhamah redeemed), 'I will say to those who were not My people, You are My people' (Lo-ammi redeemed). The people respond with the covenant formula: 'You are my God.' Paul cites 2:23 in Romans 9:25-26 as finding its initial fulfillment in the ingathering of Gentiles into the people of God — the prophetic vision, written for Israel, overflows its original frame to encompass all who are brought near through Messiah. The chapter that began with divorce papers ends with a wedding vow."
